anquil-launching-duckling\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Plan: Detect and repair disconnected metadata branches during CLI commands\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nPR #511 prevents the empty-orphan bug going forward, but users who already hit the bug and continued working have a local `entire/checkpoints/v1` with real checkpoint data on a completely disconnected history from remote (no common ancestor). Currently PR #518 handles this in `EnsureMetadataBranch` during `entire enable`, but this is the wrong place — detection should happen during the CLI commands that actually need the metadata branch (explain, rewind, resume, etc.).\\n\\n**Diverged is fine** — local and remote share a common ancestor but each has unique commits. This is normal multi-dev flow, handled by the push path's tree merge. **Disconnected is the bug state** — no common ancestor, only caused by the empty-orphan bug. This needs detection and repair.\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\n### Detection\\n\\nCheck if local and remote `entire/checkpoints/v1` are disconnected using `git merge-base`:\\n\\n```\\ngit merge-base <local-hash> <remote-hash>\\n```\\n- Exit 0 → shares ancestry (diverged or one is ancestor of other) → no action\\n- Exit non-zero, no output → disconnected → repair needed\\n\\n### Repair: cherry-pick local commits onto remote tip\\n\\n1. Walk local branch from tip to root, collect commits (oldest-first)\\n2. Skip the initial empty orphan commit (empty tree, no useful data)\\n3. Reset local branch to remote tip\\n4. For each local commit:\\n   - Compute new entries: flatten commit's tree, subtract parent's tree entries\\n   - Apply new entries onto current tip's tree\\n   - Create new commit preserving original message/author\\n5. Update local branch ref\\n\\nThis works because checkpoint shards are unique paths (`<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/`) — cherry-picks always apply cleanly. Preserves linear commit history and individual commit messages.\\n\\n### Where detection runs\\n\\n**Once per process**, triggered at the strategy layer when the checkpoint store is first accessed. Uses `sync.Once` to avoid redundant `git merge-base` calls.\\n\\n**Call sites:**\\n1. `ManualCommitStrategy.getCheckpointStore()` (`manual_commit.go:47`) — covers all strategy-mediated reads and writes (explain, rewind, resume, clean, condensation)\\n2. `getBranchCheckpoints()` (`explain.go:888`) — bypasses strategy, creates own GitStore\\n3. `ListCheckpoints()` (`strategy/common.go:112`) — opens own repo, reads branch directly\\n\\n### User-facing output\\n\\n```\\n[entire] Detected disconnected session metadata (local and remote share no common ancestor)\\n[entire] Cherry-picking 3 local checkpoint(s) onto remote...\\n[entire] Done — all local and remote checkpoints preserved\\n```\\n\\n## Files to modify\\n\\n### New file: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/metadata_reconcile.go`\\n\\nDetection + cherry-pick repair:\\n\\n- `ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch(repo *git.Repository) error` — main function\\n- `isDisconnected(repoPath, hashA, hashB string) bool` — uses `git merge-base` (not `--is-ancestor`)\\n- `collectCommitChain(repo, ref) []*object.Commit` — walks parents to root, returns oldest-first\\n- `cherryPickOnto(repo, base plumbing.Hash, commits []*object.Commit) (plumbing.Hash, error)` — applies each commit's new entries onto base\\n\\nReuses: `checkpoint.FlattenTree()`, `checkpoint.BuildTreeFromEntries()`, `GetGitAuthorFromRepo()`\\n\\n### New file: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/metadata_reconcile_test.go`\\n\\nTests using existing `initBareWithMetadataBranch` and `cloneWithConfig` helpers:\\n\\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_NoRemote` — no-op\\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_NoLocal` — no-op\\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_SameHash` — no-op\\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_SharedAncestry` — no-op (diverged, not disconnected)\\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_Disconnected` — creates disconnected orphan with local checkpoint, verifies after repair: linear history on top of remote, both local and remote data present\\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_MultipleLocalCheckpoints` — 3 local commits, all cherry-picked\\n\\n### Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go`\\n\\n- Add package-level `sync.Once` gate: `ensureMetadataReconciled(repo)`\\n- Export: `EnsureMetadataReconciled(repo *git.Repository) error` — for callers outside strategy package\\n- Remove `syncMetadataBranch` call from `EnsureMetadataBranch` (move that logic to the new reconcile function)\\n- Keep `isAncestorCLI` — still useful for the fast-forward case\\n- Add reconciliation call to `ListCheckpoints()`\\n\\n### Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit.go`\\n\\nIn `getCheckpointStore()`, add after `OpenRepository`:\\n```go\\nif err := ensureMetadataReconciled(repo); err != nil {\\n    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \\\"[entire] Warning: %v\\\\n\\\", err)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/explain.go`\\n\\nIn `getBranchCheckpoints()`, add before `checkpoint.NewGitStore(repo)`:\\n```go\\nif err := strategy.EnsureMetadataReconciled(repo); err != nil {\\n    // Log but don't fail — reads may still work\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## What happens in `EnsureMetadataBranch` after this change\\n\\n`EnsureMetadataBranch` (called during `enable`) keeps only:\\n- Create local from remote when local doesn't exist (PR #511)\\n- Replace empty orphan with remote (PR #516)\\n- Create empty orphan when neither exists\\n- Error handling for non-ref-not-found errors\\n\\nThe disconnected/diverged reconciliation logic (`syncMetadataBranch`) is removed — that responsibility moves to `ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch`.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nSpecific tests:\\n```bash\\ngo test ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/ -run TestReconcileDisconnected -v\\n```\\n\\nManual verification:\\n1. Clone repo with remote checkpoints\\n2. Create disconnected local branch (orphan with different data)\\n3. Run `go run ./cmd/entire 