ler sees the error. But looking at how the callers actually handle it, they all treat reconciliation failures as warnings and continue anyway, since this is meant to be a one-time repair operation.\\n\\nThe real question is whether we should cache the error so all callers see the warning, or if it's acceptable that only the first one logs it. I think it's fine as-is because retrying won't help — the repo state hasn't changed, and `sync.Once` is intentionally preventing retries. If we wanted to be stricter about it, we could move the error to package level so everyone sees it, but I'm not sure it's worth the added complexity.\\n\\nActually, I should just fix it. Making `reconcileErr` package-level alongside `reconcileOnce` is a one-line change and the right approach, even if it doesn't matter much in practice since the first caller already logged the warning and all callers treat it as non-fatal anyway.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":130,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":138929,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":130},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYXYdwbT6sBh4h69fJ2aK\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"5c5bfe31-9453-4002-92e0-f86c1c7390f3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T23:27:09.988Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"5c5bfe31-9453-4002-92e0-f86c1c7390f3\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/dvydra/src/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"42e0519f-9103-4bac-8c5e-804338fd82f2\",\"version\":\"2.1.59\",\"gitBranch\":\"fix/reconcile-disconnected-metadata-branch\",\"slug\":\"tranquil-launching-duckling\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_015xWqgTJgmxyCZMvMXYqMrq\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"It's technically correct but not a practical problem — all three callers treat reconcil